Gluster Filesystem is an open source clustered file system capable of
scaling to several petabytes and handling thousands of clients. Gluster
Filesystem clusters together storage building blocks over Infiniband
RDMA or TCP/IP interconnect, aggregating disk and memory resources and
managing data in a single global namespace. Gluster Filesystem is based
on a stackable user space design and can deliver exceptional performance
for diverse workloads.
